{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Phase 2 of the reconciler vendor-adapter seam (follow-up to 44be / ADR 0035)\n\nPhase 1 (`44be-2ae1-ba73-46da`) authored ADR 0035, established `adapters/jira/`, and moved the\none loader-safe, zero-patch-site module (`jira_fields.py`). Phase 2 turns the *structural* seam\ninto an *enforced-by-interface* one: it pins a backend interface, routes the core through it,\nand completes the physical migration of the remaining Jira modules ŌĆö so a second backend\n(GitHub Issues, Linear, ŌĆ”) is added by implementing `adapters/<x>/` with **no core rewrite**.\nThe concrete interface is pinned in **ADR 0035 ┬¦(d)** (`docs/adr/0035-reconciler-vendor-adapter-seam.md`);\nthis epic implements it. The first real second backend is **out of scope** here and tracked by\nepic `be74-7832-03a8-48ac` (which this epic `blocks`).\n\n## Design (decided)\n\n- rebar's own local ticket is the canonical model ŌĆö **no separate `CanonicalTicket`**; adapters\n  translate vendorŌćälocal via the existing mappers.\n- The core owns diff/apply; adapters only read + enact.\n- Five role Protocols (`TicketTransport`, `OutboundMapper`, `InboundMapper`, `FieldSanitizer`,\n  `IdentityConvention`) behind one `Backend` facade, + opt-in capability Protocols.\n- One new type `RemoteRef{vendor, instance, remote_id}` replaces the hardcoded `\"jira\"` literal.\n- An in-tree decorator registry + `select_backend(config.reconciler.backend)`.\n\n## Child decomposition (non-overlapping; strict dependency chain S1ŌåÆS2ŌåÆS3ŌåÆS4ŌåÆS5)\n\n1. **S1 `ef33-eaf6-a545-4bfb`** ŌĆö pin the interface in ADR 0035 ┬¦(d) (docs only).\n2. **S2 `ce4d-c3ca-5412-4798`** ŌĆö define the `Backend` Protocols + `RemoteRef` + a backend-\n   agnostic contract suite + a thin `JiraBackend` (zero behavior change). *No core rewiring.*\n3. **S3 `94f9-a9a0-7475-4e75`** ŌĆö selection infrastructure **only**: add `reconciler.backend`\n   config (static-key validated) + an in-tree registry + `select_backend()` + `JiraBackend`\n   registration. *No consumer rewiring* (deferred to S4, because the `_load_acli` seam returns a\n   module and changing its contract must land atomically with its patched tests).\n4. **S4 `6673-7636-a116-4f90`** ŌĆö route **every core consumer** through the `Backend` port: the\n   8 confirmed vendor-importing core modules **and** the 4 transport/construction sites\n   (`applier`/`fetcher`/`run_differs`/`_attestation`); move ADF-sizing + lossy-status/parent +\n   duplicated maps/link-constants into `adapters/jira/`. *Changes callers, not file locations.*\n5. **S5 `dfb9-d2d1-455d-48d9`** ŌĆö physically relocate `acli*`/`adf`/`outbound_fields`/\n   `comment_limits` into `adapters/jira/`, teach the file-location loader the new dir, and\n   migrate the ~29 test patch strings atomically (no shims).\n\nThe boundary between stories is: **S2 = interface**, **S3 = selection primitive (infra only)**,\n**S4 = who-calls-what (route all consumers, core neutrality)**, **S5 = where-files-live (physical\nmove)** ŌĆö disjoint edit-sets, each independently reviewable and behavior-preserving.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] ADR 0035 ┬¦(d) pins the interface (S1); the `Backend` Protocols, `RemoteRef`, and a\n  contract suite passing against both `JiraBackend` and a test-only `FakeBackend` exist (S2).\n- [ ] The backend is chosen by `config.reconciler.backend` via the registry; the default\n  (`\"jira\"`) reproduces today's behavior end-to-end (S3).\n- [ ] After S4 the backend-neutral **core** no longer imports `adapters.jira.*` or the root\n  vendor modules ŌĆö enforced by a neutrality gate on the 10 differ/apply sites. (The vendor files\n  still physically reside at the package root after S4; only their *callers* change here. Their\n  physical relocation into `adapters/jira/` completes in S5 ŌĆö so the full \"vendor code lives only\n  under adapters/jira/\" predicate is an S5 outcome, not an S4 one.)\n- [ ] `acli*`/`adf`/`outbound_fields`/`comment_limits` reside under `adapters/jira/`, the loader\n  resolves the location-pinned modules there, the two non-moved root modules that reference them\n  by sibling filename (`inbound_fields.py`, `outbound_comments.py`) are repointed, and all ~29\n  test patch strings are migrated with no re-export shims (S5).\n- [ ] Every `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/*.py` stays within the 800-LOC module-size cap\n  (`.github/module-size-limit.txt`) throughout.\n- [ ] Full suite (`make lint && make typecheck && make test`) green at every landed change; no\n  behavior regression vs. the pre-epic baseline (all changes are behavior-preserving).\n- [ ] Epic `be74` (first real second backend) is unblocked: adding a backend requires only a new\n  `adapters/<x>/` implementing the pinned interface ŌĆö verified by the proof-of-seam\n  `FakeBackend` passing the contract suite with no core edit."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784698075376291001,"uuid":"42e58d29-05c3-4023-a921-8e2929e0cde3"}